Reasoning: 
1. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on developing a novel scalable graph-based semi-supervised learning method, which falls under the domain of machine learning. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed method involves learning a small set of vertexes to characterize the high-dense regions of the input data, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. 
3. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): The proposed method is evaluated on real datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision and pattern recognition tasks. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper proposes a novel approach to construct the graph of the input data from the learned graph of a small number of vertexes, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures. 
5. cs.CL (Computation and Language): The proposed method can be applied to text classification tasks, which fall under the domain of computation and language.
